'''Aaron Demsky''' is professor of biblical history at [[Bar-Ilan University]].  He is an [[epigrapher]] noted for his work on [[onomastics]].<ref name=Shanks>{{cite book|last1=[[Hershel Shanks]]|title=Freeing the Dead Sea Scrolls|date=2010|publisher=Bloomsbury|isbn=144111713X|page=218}}</ref><ref name=DemskyBialikPrize/>

Demsky is the winner of the 2014 [[Bialik Prize]] for his book, ''Literacy in Ancient Israel''.<ref name="Bialik Prize">{{cite web|url=http://www1.biu.ac.il/indexE.php?id=14105&pt=8&pid=33&level=2&cPath=33,14105|title=Prof. Aaron Demsky Awarded Bialik Prize for Jewish Scholarship|publisher=Bar Ilan University|accessdate=9 November 2015}}</ref><ref name=DemskyBialikPrize>{{cite news|last1=Grave-Lazee|first1=Lidar|title=Demsky to receive Bialik Prize|url=http://www.jpost.com/National-News/Demsky-to-receive-Bialik-Prize-360996|accessdate=9 November 2015|publisher=[[Jerusalem Post]]|date=30 June 2014}}</ref><ref name=JewishThoughtAward>{{cite news|last1=Klein|first1=Steven|title=Prof. Aaron Demsky to receive Jewish Thought award|url=http://www.haaretz.com/.premium-1.602945|accessdate=9 November 2015|publisher=[[Haaretz]]|date=3 July 2014}}</ref>

