{{Gaza Strip}} The '''Governorates of the Gaza Strip''' are 5 administrative districts, ruled since 2007 by the [[Hamas Government in Gaza]]. After the signing of the [[Oslo Accords]] in 1993, the [[Palestinian territories]] of the [[West Bank]] and [[Gaza Strip]] were divided into three areas ([[Administrative divisions of the Oslo Accords|Area A, Area B, and Area C]]) and 16 [[governorate]]s under the jurisdiction of the [[Palestinian National Authority]]. In 2005, Israel withdrew from the Gaza Strip, enlarging the administered Palestinian territories in that region. In 2007, following the [[Battle of Gaza (2007)|War of Brothers]] in the Gaza Strip between Fatah and Hamas, the later took over the area and expelled all Palestinian Authority officials, affiliated with Fatah.
