{{Infobox mountain | name = Piton de la Petite Rivière Noire | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 828 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 828 | prominence_ref = | map = Mauritius | map_caption = Location of Piton de la Petite Rivière Noire in Mauritius | map_size = 220 | label_position = right | listing = [[List of countries by highest point|Country high point]] | location = [[Mauritius]] | range = | coordinates = {{coord|20|24|S|57|28|E|type:mountain_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | topo = | type = [[Hill]] | age = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Piton de la Petite Rivière Noire''' (''Little Black River Peak'') is the highest mountain on the island of [[Mauritius]], in the [[Indian Ocean]]. Located in the [[Rivière Noire District]] and rising to a height of 828&nbsp;m (2717&nbsp;ft) above sea level, it forms part of the Black River mountain range.
There are two other main mountain ranges in Mauritius: Moka-Port Louis and Grand Port-Savanne. The Moka-Port Louis range includes [[Pieter Both (mountain)|Pieter Both]] (820 m) and Le Pouce (811 m) mountains, the second and third highest summits respectively. Both are more famous than Piton de la Petite Rivière Noire in the southwest.
