'''Ponta Baleia''' (Portuguese for "whale point") is a headland and a settlement in the south of [[Caué District]] on [[São Tomé Island]] in [[São Tomé and Príncipe]]. Its population is 43 (2012 census).<ref name=census12>[https://www.ine.st/phocadownload/userupload/Documentos/DADOS%20LOCALIDADE%20PROJE%C3%87%C3%95ES/Publica%C3%A7%C3%A3o%20dos%20Resultados%20sobre%20Localidades%20-%20IV%20RGPH%202012.pdf 2012 detailed census São Tomé e Príncipe], [[Instituto Nacional de Estatística (São Tomé and Príncipe)|Instituto Nacional de Estatística]]</ref> The locality lies 1.5 km east of [[Porto Alegre, São Tomé and Príncipe|Porto Alegre]] and 2 km southeast of [[Vila Malanza]]. A ferry goes from Ponta Baleia to [[Ilhéu das Rolas]].
